Complementing to the [[Real_world_shops]] and [[Trade]] pages, this page will contain a list of organizations that do not revolve around Bitcion, but have added Bitcoin as a supported means of payment or donation.

* [WordPress,](https://wordpress.com/) a blog web hosting service provider, is   [accepting payments in bitcoins](http://en.blog.wordpress.com/2012/11/15/pay-another-way-bitcoin/).
* [Diaspora](https://joindiaspora.com/), the p2p Facebook alternative, are [accepting Bitcoin donations](https://www.diasporafoundation.org/donate).
* [Wiki Leaks](http://wikileaks.org/) accept [Bitcoin donations](http://shop.wikileaks.org/donate)
* [JJGames.com](http://www.jjgames.com/), used console games, 5% discount for Bitcoin payments with "Bitcoin" promotional code
* [DOSBox](http://dosbox.com/), an x86 emulator with DOS (the address is under the [Crew](http://www.dosbox.com/crew.php) section)
* [Occupy Wallstreet](http://www.nycga.net/) accept [Bitcoin donations](http://www.nycga.net/how-to-help/)
* [Gadgets Direct](http://www.gadgetsdirect.com.au/) now accepts Bitcoins for over 15,500 Gadgets all with Free Worldwide Shipping.
* [Wuala, online storage/backup](http://www.wuala.com/en/bitcoin)
* [PM AKORDEON Record Label](http://pmakordeoneditora.pt/) accepts Bitcoin on its [Online Music Shop](http://loja.pmakordeoneditora.pt/)
* [Memory Dealers](http://www.memorydealers.com/)
* [BioStim Pty Ltd](http://www.biostim.com.au/) now accepts Bitcoins for fertilisers and health products.
* [Lokad, demand forecasting service](http://www.lokad.com/)
* [OKPAY](https://www.okpay.com/), a payment processor, [now supports Bitcoin](https://www.okpay.com/en/company/news/okpay-bitcoin.html)
* [Switch Poker](https://www.switchpoker.com/), an established poker site, [just added Bitcoin](http://www.marketwatch.com/story/switchpokercom-adds-controversial-virtual-currency-bitcoin-as-deposit-and-withdrawal-method-2011-11-22)
* [uploaded.to](http://uploaded.to/), one click file hoster
* [Cigs.eu](http://www.cigs.eu/) European Cigarette retailer now accepts Bitcoin.
* [Exoware](http://www.exoware.net), ISP, web hosting, VPS provider, domain names, SSL certificates
* [Texas Laser Systems](http://www.texaslasersystems.com/) Supplier of quality lasers, components, and accessories located in Fort Worth, Texas.
* [The Internet Archive](http://www.archive.org/) is a non-profit that was founded to build an Internet library. They accept bitcoin [donations](http://www.archive.org/donate/index.php).
* [NinjaBoot USB Privacy Drive](https://ninjaboot.com/) now accepting Bitcoins for bootable USB drives that protect privacy and anonymity with Tor.
